data.title: Noomi Rapace Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Noomi Rapace with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Moved to Iceland with her mother and stepfather when she was 5

Made her acting debut in an Icelandic film when she was 7

She and her husband chose their surname, Rapace, together; it means 'bird of prey' in French

Her mother, Nina Nor√©n, played her character's mother in The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo (2009)

Got several body piercings to play Lisbeth Salander, but refused to get any tattoos

Made her English-speaking acting debut in Sherlock Holmes: Game of Shadows (2011)
